SafeSitePlus: Safety Guidelines & Compliance Documents 
1. Safety Guidelines 
1.1 General Site Safety Rules 
1. Always wear required PPE (helmets, safety boots, gloves, and eye protection). 
2. Unauthorized personnel are not allowed on the construction site. 
3. All workers must complete safety training before starting work. 
4. Keep work areas clean and free from hazards. 
5. Report any unsafe conditions immediately to the supervisor. 
1.2 Working at Heights 
1. Harnesses and lifelines must be used if working at heights above 6 feet. 
2. Ladders and scaffolds must be inspected daily. 
3. Workers must not carry heavy loads while climbing ladders. 
1.3 Heavy Machinery & Equipment Use 
1. Only trained personnel are allowed to operate machinery.

2. Pre-use inspections are mandatory for all equipment. 
3. Never bypass safety mechanisms (e.g., emergency stop buttons). 
4. Stay out of machine operation zones unless authorized. 
1.4 Electrical Safety 
1. Lockout/Tagout procedures must be followed before maintenance. 
2. Damaged wires or outlets must be reported immediately. 
3. Only authorized electricians can perform electrical work. 
1.5 Fire Safety 
1. Fire extinguishers must be accessible in all high-risk areas. 
2. No smoking is allowed in hazardous zones. 
3. Flammable materials must be stored in designated areas. 
 
2. Safety Guidelines & Compliance Documents 
2.1 OSHA Regulations (Occupational Safety and Health Administration) 
• Fall Protection: Required when working at heights over 6 feet.

• Machine Guarding: All moving parts must have protective barriers. 
• Noise Control: Hearing protection required above 85 dB. 
• Respiratory Safety: Workers in dusty or chemical-exposed areas must wear N95+ masks. 
• Emergency Exits: Must be unblocked and clearly marked at all times. 
2.2 PPE (Personal Protective Equipment) Guidelines 
• Mandatory PPE: Helmet, gloves, safety boots, eye protection, high-visibility vest. 
• Special PPE (for welding, toxic material handling): Face shields, respirators, chemical-resistant 
gloves. 
• Replacement & Inspection: PPE should be inspected before every shift. 
2.3 Emergency Response Protocols 
Fire Emergency 
1. Activate the nearest fire alarm. 
2. Evacuate using the nearest exit (avoid elevators).

3. Use fire extinguishers only if trained and fire is manageable. 
Medical Emergency 
1. Call emergency services immediately (1122 or 911). 
2. Provide first aid if trained. 
3. Keep the area clear for responders. 
Chemical Spill Response 
1. Isolate the affected area. 
2. Use spill kits and wear protective gloves/masks. 
3. Report to the supervisor immediately. 
 
3. Site-Specific Information 
3.1 Floor Plans & Hazard Zones 
Zone 1: High-risk area – Heavy machinery in use. 
Zone 2: PPE mandatory – Welding and chemical storage. 
Zone 3: No unauthorized access – Electrical maintenance zone. 
3.2 Worker Shift Schedules 
• Morning Shift: 7:00 AM – 3:00 PM

• Evening Shift: 3:00 PM – 11:00 PM 
• Night Shift: 11:00 PM – 7:00 AM 
3.3 Equipment Maintenance Logs 
Equipment Last Maintenance Date Next Scheduled Maintenance 
Excavator-01 15 Feb 2024 15 March 2024 
Crane-07 10 Feb 2024 10 March 2024 
Welding Machine-03 20 Jan 2024 20 April 2024 
 
4. Company Circulars 
4.1 Ramadan Timings 
• Morning Shift: 8:00 AM – 2:00 PM 
• Evening Shift: 2:00 PM – 8:00 PM 
• Night Shift: 8:00 PM – 2:00 AM 
4.2 Eid Holidays 
• Eid-ul-Fitr: 10 April – 13 April 2024 
• Eid-ul-Adha: 15 June – 18 June 2024 
4.3 Absent Policy 
• Uninformed Absence: 2 warnings → Suspension 
• Late Arrival: More than 3 late arrivals → Deduction from salary 
• Emergency Leave: Must be approved 24 hours in advance
